## Why this layer exists

- **Coordinate without a monorepo.** The members are coupled (they change together, share norms) but must stay independent repos — each linkable and ownable on its own. A monorepo would bind them architecturally; a meta layer coordinates them without that cost.
- **Give the AI the full picture.** Working one member blind to the others drifts. Running coordination from here — with this file and the siblings in view — is the anti-drift mechanism, by context and norms rather than check scripts.
- **A reusable pattern.** The same "meta layer over N independent repos" shape is shared with `claude-meta`, `bootcamp-rocket-meta`, and other clusters.

## How the family is wired

- **Pointer, not container.** This layer points at the member repos; it never holds their files. The real repos live at `~/Developer/{{PREFIX}}-*` (the single source of truth); they are **not** mirrored in-tree here — reach them at the relative paths `../{{PREFIX}}-*`. A committed `{{PREFIX}}-meta.code-workspace` (under `.vscode/`) lists every member as a VS Code root for human review.
- **Naming.** Members are `{{PREFIX}}-<token>`; this layer is `{{PREFIX}}-meta`. A new member needs no wiring here — reach it at `../{{PREFIX}}-<token>` like the rest.
- **Git ceremony.** Follows the shared `*-meta` ceremony — subject-only Conventional Commits, **no `Co-Authored-By`** (members, as content repos, *do* keep the trailer). The members keep their own git lifecycles; confirm per repo.
- **Provenance.** Per-member `LICENSE`. Each member owns its own git / remote / visibility setup; this layer does not track that state.

## Working across the family

- **The coupling rule.** A convention worth keeping in one member is often worth carrying to the others. When you touch shared structure in one, check whether the siblings want the same move.
- **Run coordination from here.** This file loads only in `{{PREFIX}}-meta` sessions, so cross-member work should be driven from this layer — reach the siblings at `../{{PREFIX}}-*` (the workspace lists them too). Scope `Grep`/`Glob` to those sibling paths explicitly; a bare `.` search stays inside this repo and won't reach them. Commits still land in each real repo (`~/Developer/{{PREFIX}}-*`), never here.
- **When a new member joins**, author a matching per-member memory card in this repo's memory store (what it is + where its own docs live + one durable gotcha).

## North star & judgment frame

- **Personal-fit is the hard constraint.** These repos serve the maintainer's own workflow first; when fitting that workflow conflicts with outside reusability, personal-fit wins. Hard-coded preferences and Chinese READMEs are deliberate.
{{#同型}}
- **Each member concrete and closed; the family open.** A finished member is frozen as a record; the architecture appends new members of the same kind without committing to any particular future one.
{{/同型}}
{{#混合}}
- **Concrete and closed today, architecturally open tomorrow.** Ship one concrete thing, leave the architecture open. The cluster starts with its current members and neither precludes nor commits to more.
{{/混合}}
